= Hypocricy (Nifāq)

*Definition*:
- Linguistically: To conceal something and hide it.
- In Islām : To outwardly show Islām while concealing disbelief and evil inwardly.

== Types of Hypocrisy:

There are two types:
	1.	Major (Creedal) Hypocrisy – Nifāq Akbar I‘tiqadi
	2.	Minor (Practical) Hypocrisy – Nifāq Asghar ‘Amali



== 1. Major (Creedal) Hypocrisy: 

*Definition*:

This is the greater form of hypocrisy where a person outwardly displays Islām but inwardly conceals disbelief.

*Ruling:*

It removes a person completely from the religion. Allāh has prepared for such people the lowest depths of Hell.

Evidence: #quran-block[إِنَّ ٱلۡمُنَٰفِقِينَ فِي ٱلدَّرۡكِ ٱلۡأَسۡفَلِ مِنَ ٱلنَّارِ وَلَن تَجِدَ لَهُمۡ نَصِيرًا ١٤٥
][Indeed, the hypocrites will be in the lowest depths of the Fire—and you will never find for them a helper.
(An-Nisā’ Q4:145)]



*Types of Major (Creedal) Hypocrisy:*

1.    Denying the Prophet #pbuh 
2.	Denying some of what the Messenger #pbuh) came with.
3.	Complete hatred of the Messenger #pbuh.
4.	Hatred toward some of what the Messenger #pbuh came with.
5.	Feeling joy at the decline of the Prophet’s religion #pbuh.
6.	Hating the victory of the Prophet’s religion #pbuh.


== 2. Minor (Practical) Hypocrisy:

*Definition:*

Doing one or more actions from the actions of hypocrites while still having faith in the heart.

*Ruling:*
	It does not expel one from Islām but it is forbidden and considered among the major sins. The person will have a mix of faith and hypocrisy and if such traits increase, the person becomes a pure hypocrite in practice.


*Examples of Minor Hypocrisy:*
	1.	Lying when speaking, as is mentioned in the hadith “When he speaks, he lies.”
	2.	Breaking promises, as the prophet said #salamHIM said “When he makes a promise, he breaks it.”
	3.	Betraying trust, the Prophet #pbuh said “When he is entrusted, he betrays.”
	4.	Behaving immorally in disputes, it is also mentioned in the hadith “When he argues, he behaves wickedly.”
	5.	Breaking pledges, the Prophet #pbuh also said “When he makes a covenant, he is treacherous.”

	6.	Laziness in performing prayer in congregation at the mosque: Allāh says: #quran-block[إِنَّ ٱلۡمُنَٰفِقِينَ يُخَٰدِعُونَ ٱللَّهَ وَهُوَ خَٰدِعُهُمۡ وَإِذَا قَامُوٓاْ إِلَى ٱلصَّلَوٰةِ قَامُواْ كُسَالَىٰ يُرَآءُونَ ٱلنَّاسَ وَلَا يَذۡكُرُونَ ٱللَّهَ إِلَّا قَلِيلٗا ١٤٢
][Indeed, the hypocrites [think to] deceive Allah, but He is deceiving them. *And when they stand for prayer, they stand lazily,* showing [themselves to] the people and not remembering Allah except a little. (An-Nisā’ Q4:142)]
 

	7.	Showing off in righteous deeds (Riya’). Allāh says:  #quran-block[إِنَّ ٱلۡمُنَٰفِقِينَ يُخَٰدِعُونَ ٱللَّهَ وَهُوَ خَٰدِعُهُمۡ وَإِذَا قَامُوٓاْ إِلَى ٱلصَّلَوٰةِ قَامُواْ كُسَالَىٰ يُرَآءُونَ ٱلنَّاسَ وَلَا يَذۡكُرُونَ ٱللَّهَ إِلَّا قَلِيلٗا ١٤٢
][Indeed, the hypocrites [think to] deceive Allah, but He is deceiving them. And when they stand for prayer, they stand lazily, *showing [themselves to] the people and not remembering Allah except a little.* (An-Nisā’ Q4:142)]